The speaker refers to the process of opening the Tiny Shakespeare file in preparation for examination and subsequent usage in the 'ChatGPT' neural network model they are explaining and building upon throughout the talk. Specifically, this phrase "Here, I open the "input" means that the speaker is opening the file containing the 'Tiny Shakespeare' dataset. This dataset, which contains a concatenation of all the works of Shakespeare, will be used to train the 'ChatGPT' model, helping it learn how words follow one another in sequence and allowing the network to predict and generate language that resembles Shakespeare's writing style.